    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i've been watching the pigeons in the park for the last three weeks and its getting weird. they aren't just flying around, they are following specific geometric patterns right before a storm hits. like, if they fly in a tight spiral near the fountain, i know exactly how many minutes until it pours. i think i've finally cracked how they signal weather changes through their flight paths. have u ever heard of anything like this?",
